SIMPLE: supposition
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Supposition
<hw>Sup`po*si"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>supposition</ets>, L. <ets>suppositio</ets> a placing under, a
substitution, fr. <ets>supponere</ets>, <ets>suppositium</ets>, to put
under, to substitute. The word has the meaning corresponding to
<ets>suppose</ets>. See <er>Sub-</er>, and <er>Position</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of supposing, laying down, imagining, or
considering as true or existing, what is known not to be true, or what
is not proved.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is supposed; hypothesis; conjecture;
surmise; opinion or belief without sufficient evidence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This is only an infallibility upon <qex>supposition</qex> that if
a thing be true, it is imposible to be false.</q>
<rj><qau>Tillotson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He means are in <qex>supposition</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suppositional</ent>⟦br⟧
